# Phase 1: 核心架构搭建 (The Foundation)

## Goal
Establish the WPF project with MVVM pattern, integrate essential libraries, and define core data models.

## Proposed Changes

### Project Structure (Manual Creation)
Since the .NET SDK is not detected in the environment, the project files will be created manually.

- Create solution `GeminiLauncher.sln`
- Create WPF project `GeminiLauncher`
- Create essential source files:
    - `GeminiLauncher.csproj`: Define dependencies (WPF UI, Newtonsoft.Json, SharpZipLib).
    - `App.xaml` / `App.xaml.cs`: Application entry point.
    - `MainWindow.xaml` / `MainWindow.xaml.cs`: Main window.
    - `ViewModels/MainViewModel.cs`: Core view logic.

### Dependencies (via .csproj)
The `GeminiLauncher.csproj` will include `PackageReference` for:
- `WPF-UI`
- `Newtonsoft.Json`
- `SharpZipLib`
- `CommunityToolkit.Mvvm`

### Data Models
#### [NEW] `Models/GameInstance.cs`
- Properties: `Version`, `GameDir`, `Mods`, `JavaPath`, `JvmArgs`.

#### [NEW] `Models/Account.cs`
- Properties: `Username`, `Uuid`, `AccessToken`, `AccountType` (Offline/Microsoft).

#### [NEW] `Services/ConfigService.cs`
- Features: Load/Save global settings (DownloadSource, MaxRam, JavaInstallations).

## Verification Plan
### Automated Tests
- Unit tests for `GameInstance` parsing logic (later).
- Unit tests for `ConfigService` read/write.

### Manual Verification
- Launch the blank app window.
- Verify "WPF UI" styles are applied.
- Verify `ConfigService` creates a config file on startup.
